                <head>271. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The President’s Intelligence Checklist, August 23, seen by the President,
                    contains the following item entitled “South Vietnam”: <list>
                        <item>“a. Tight security precautions are still being enforced in Saigon and
                            Hue, but troop presence is less obtrusive.</item>
                        <item>“b. <persName corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> told a US source
                            yesterday that the generals recommended the imposition of martial law.
                            He denied this amounted to a coup, but warned it could become one if
                                <persName corresp="#p_DIEM1">Diem</persName> vacillated or
                            compromised on the Buddhist issue.</item>
                        <item>“c. Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> notes
                            that the resignation of Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_MAU1"
                                >Mau</persName> ‘obviously caught the government flatfooted’.”
                                (<persName corresp="#p_KJE1">Kennedy</persName> Library, National
                            Security Files, <persName corresp="#p_CMGCV1">Chester V.
                                Clifton</persName> Series)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
